{"sha": "e88d863cbde6ee90709d291670a843346f84d3b6", "node_id": "MDY6Q29tbWl0MTM2NTMxMDA6ZTg4ZDg2M2NiZGU2ZWU5MDcwOWQyOTE2NzBhODQzMzQ2Zjg0ZDNiNg==", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Jonathan Wakely", "email": "jwakely@redhat.com", "date": "2019-06-25T13:18:36Z"}, "committer": {"name": "Jonathan Wakely", "email": "redi@gcc.gnu.org", "date": "2019-06-25T13:18:36Z"}, "message": "Fix non-portable use of std::abs(double) in constexpr function\n\nAlthough libstdc++ adds 'constexpr' to its std::abs(floating-point)\noverloads (as a non-conforming extension), those overloads are not used\nif the target libc provides them, which is the case on Solaris.\n\nThe fix is to avoid std::abs and simply apply the negation when needed.\n\n\t* include/std/numeric (midpoint(T, T)): Avoid std::abs in constexpr\n\tfunction.\n\nFrom-SVN: r272653", "tree": {"sha": "ca3250791e2d84089352d0a3ea60b47fbcef317e", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/git/trees/ca3250791e2d84089352d0a3ea60b47fbcef317e"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/git/commits/e88d863cbde6ee90709d291670a843346f84d3b6", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commits/e88d863cbde6ee90709d291670a843346f84d3b6", "html_url": "https://github.com/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commit/e88d863cbde6ee90709d291670a843346f84d3b6", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commits/e88d863cbde6ee90709d291670a843346f84d3b6/comments", "author": {"login": "jwakely", "id": 1254480, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEyNTQ0ODA=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1254480?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jwakely", "html_url": "https://github.com/jwakely", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jwakely/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jwakely/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jwakely/gis